value.name: Mount Pico - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Mount Pico (Portuguese: Montanha do Pico) is a currently quiescent stratovolcano located on Pico Island, in the mid-Atlantic archipelago of the Azores. It is the highest mountain in Portugal , at 2,351 metres (7,713 ft) above sea level, and is one of the highest Atlantic mountains; it is more than twice the elevation of any other peak in the Azores.

value.name: Climbing Mount Pico: What You Need to Know - Geeky Explorer
value.snippet: Standing high from its 2,351 meters of altitude, Montanha do Pico (Mount Pico) in Pico island is the highest peak in Portugal and the third highest in the Atlantic Ocean. All climbers – with or without guide – need to check-in in Casa da Montanha .

value.name: Hiking Mount Pico | The ONLY GUIDE YOU NEED for the Climb - TripTins
value.snippet: Well, Mount Pico on the island of Pico gives you that once in a lifetime opportunity. At 7,713 feet in elevation (2,351 meters), the dormant volcano of Mount Pico stands above the rest and is one of the most prominent sites among the Azorean islands. The good news is that anyone with the will and fitness to get to the top of the volcano can do so.

value.name: Climbing Mount Pico: How to Climb Portugal’s Tallest Mountain
value.snippet: Climbing Pico is actually made up of two mountains: Pico (which was once a volcano) and a very small “mountain” inside the crater that’s called “Piquinho.” Although Piquinho is technically an extra mountain, nobody stops at the crater: pretty much everyone climbs up Piquinho as well (10-15 minutes of scrambling). Piquinho. When visibility is good on the top of Pico, you’ll be able to see some of the other islands.

value.name: Mount Pico Azores | Portugal Visitor - Travel Guide To Portugal
value.snippet: Mount Pico (Montanha do Pico) Mount Pico on the island of Pico in the Azores archipelago is Portugal's highest mountain. The mountain stands at a height of 2,351 meters (7,712 feet). Its conical shape can be seen from everywhere on the island and on clear days from the other islands in the so-called "Triangle" - namely Faial and São Jorge.

value.name: Mount Pico Climb – Pico Island Adventures
value.snippet: Mt. Pico is the highest point in Portugal and one of the highest peaks in the Atlantic Ocean. To climb the 2.351m high mountains is one of the most exciting adventures available in the Atlantic Ocean. After a 3-4h hike you reach the Crater. From there you have a stunning view to the 5 Islands of the Central group of the Azores.
